BHADDER Boiz Music Group (BBMG) promises music acts greater future The management of Bhadder Boiz Music Group has promised the five music acts on its wings a greater future in the African music scene and global music scene.   Man of God: Bolanle Austen-Peters’ new film makes Netflix…     Seven celebrities who remarried ex-spouses     What happens when you argue with a fool – Tiwa Savage   BBMG, home to Nessy Bee, Vyce Carter, Super Pimpin, Beambo Taylor, and Dynamikal, is currently happy with the accomplishments of its music acts and promises to continue to reward them with a greater future. The record label, which was created in 2016, is co-owned by Bada Temilayo, Bada Temibayo, and Akintola Hammed. With Nessy Bee being the first act to get signed on the label, the management recently noted that it is poised to give a platform to talented artists to express their musical creativity, manage the development and arrangement of songs, manage talent, music production, creative marketing, and music distribution.